title: Storm Doris causes further Colwyn Bay pier collapse - BBC News
text:
Storm Doris causes further Colwyn Bay pier collapse 23 February 2017 Image caption Victoria Pier Storm Doris has caused a further collapse of Colwyn Bay's Victoria Pier. 
A section of the lower end of the pier had already partially collapsed into the sea earlier this month. 
Today's high winds and waves have caused damage to the seaward end of structure. 
A Conwy council spokesperson said officers will inspect the pier at low tide. The incident has been reported to the coastguard. 
Engineers and health and safety officers are monitoring the scene.
